"title": "3254: Holy Spirit, fruit of",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "3254: holy spirit, fruit of",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>The living presence of the Holy Spirit in believers leads to Christlike virtues within them, just as a living tree will bear good fruit.</p>\n<h2>God expects his people to bear spiritual fruit</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa5:4\">ISA 5:4</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt7:12-Matt7:20\">MAT 7:12–7:20</a> <em>“fruit” is a term used to indicate the produce or outcome of a person's life</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John15:8\">JHN 15:8</a></p>\n<h2>The fruit of the Spirit leads to believers becoming Christlike</h2>\n<h3>The gift of the Spirit begins this lifelong process</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor3:18\">2CO 3:18</a></strong></p>\n<h3>Christlike qualities are contrasted with sinful ones</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal5:16-Gal5:17\">GAL 5:16–5:17</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom8:5-Rom8:14\">ROM 8:5–8:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor12:7\">1CO 12:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal6:8\">GAL 6:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph5:8-Eph5:16\">EPH 5:8–5:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col3:1-Col3:17\">COL 3:1–3:17</a></p>\n<h2>The fruit of Spirit-filled living</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal5:22-Gal5:23\">GAL 5:22–5:23</a></strong> <em>“fruit” is singular, emphasising that these qualities are mutually dependent aspects of Christian living.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph5:9\">EPH 5:9</a></p>\n<h2>Examples of the fruit of the Spirit</h2>\n<h3>Love</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom5:5\">ROM 5:5</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor13:1-1Cor13:13\">1CO 13:1–13:13</a></p>\n<h3>Joy</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phil1:18-Phil1:19\">PHP 1:18–1:19</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Thess1:6\">1TH 1:6</a></p>\n<h3>Peace</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom8:6\">ROM 8:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom14:17\">ROM 14:17</a></p>\n<h3>Patience</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb6:12\">HEB 6:12</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jas5:7-Jas5:11\">JAS 5:7–5:11</a></p>\n<h3>Kindness</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor6:6\">2CO 6:6</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col3:12\">COL 3:12</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Pet1:7\">2PE 1:7</a></p>\n<h3>Goodness</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom15:14\">ROM 15:14</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Pet1:5\">2PE 1:5</a></p>\n<h3>Faithfulness</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor10:13\">1CO 10:13</a> <em>God's faithfulness is also here presented as the reason for faithfulness</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/3John1:3\">3JN 1:3</a></p>\n<h3>Gentleness</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt11:29-Matt11:30\">MAT 11:29–11:30</a> <em>Jesus Christ displays such gentleness</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Thess2:7\">1TH 2:7</a></p>\n<h3>Self-control</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Tim3:3\">2TI 3:3</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Pet1:6\">2PE 1:6</a></p>\n<h2>Other evidence of the Holy Spirit's activity</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom14:17\">ROM 14:17</a> <em>righteousness</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom15:13\">ROM 15:13</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal5:5\">GAL 5:5</a>; \n<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph1:17\">EPH 1:17</a> <em>wisdom</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph5:18\">EPH 5:18</a> <em>temperance</em></p>\n<h2>The evidence of the fruit of the Spirit is a result of divine activity, not of human effort</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor3:9\">1CO 3:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor3:16\">1CO 3:16</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal2:20\">GAL 2:20</a></p>",
